<h2>Machaut: Ay mi!</h2>

<dl>
<dt>Machaut: Ay mi!</dt>
<dd>Lais et virelais<br>
Emmanuel Bonnardot<br>
<i>Opus 111 30-171</i></dd>
</dl>

<p>Reissued in <i><a href="op1-2004.htm">Opus 111 2004</a></i>.</p>

<h3>Contents:</h3>
<p><ol>
<li>Quant je suis mis au retour (virelai; voice, fiddle)</li>
<li>Dou mal qui m'a longuement (virelai; voice, fiddle)</li>
<li>C'est force faire (virelai; fiddle)</li>
<li>Loyaut&eacute; que point ne delay (lai; voice, fiddle)</li>
<li>Douce dame jolie (virelai; rebec)</li>
<li>Mors sui se je ne vous voy (virelai &agrave; 2; voice, vihuela
d'arco)</li>
<li>Ay mi! Dame de valour (virelai; voice)</li>
<li>H&eacute; dame de valour (virelai; fiddle)</li>
<li>Moult sui de bonne heure nee (virelai &agrave; 2; voice, vihuela
d'arco)</li>
<li>H&eacute;las! et comment (virelai; cittern)</li>
<li>Comment qu'a moy lonteinne (virelai; voice, cittern)</li>
<li>Le lay de plour (lai; voice, fiddle, cittern)</li>
<li>Dame, je weil endurer (virelai; vihuela d'arco)</li>
</ol></p>

<p>Performer: Emmanuel Bonnardot (voice, fiddle, rebec, cittern,
vihuela d'arco)</p>

<p>Playing time: 55'</p>

<p>Recording date: June 1996 (Bretagne)</p>

<p>Reviewed in:<br>
Fanfare (Vol./#-p.): 21/3- (January/February 1998)
</p>

<p>This recording emphasizes Machaut's monophonic writing, including
just two polyphonic tracks.  The others are accompanied by drone,
which serves to underscore certain melodic figures.  The performance
practice dates back to Binkley and beyond, but there is little to
confirm it one way or another in 14th century sources.</p>

<p>This is a highly polished rendition.  Note track transposition
between CD &amp; liner notes at 7 &amp; 8.</p>

<p>A recording by the present performer and others, which connects
Machaut's music with that of the previous generation:</p>

<dl>
<dt>Machaut et l'art des Trouv&egrave;res</dt>
<dd>Vi&egrave;les et voix du Moyen Age<br>
Emmanuel Bonnardot et al.<br>
<i><a href="clp9308.htm">Calliope 9308</a></i></dd>
</dl>

<p>A program devoted explicitly to the lais of the previous
generation:</p>

<dl>
<dt>Tristan et Yseut</dt>
<dd>Alla Francesca - Brigitte Lesne &amp; Pierre Hamon<br>
<i><a href="zzt51002.htm">Zig-Zag Territoires 051002</a></i></dd>
</dl>

<p>And a program which presents both Machaut's longest lai, and
other complementary pieces in the genre:</p>

<dl>
<dt>L'amoureus tourment</dt>
<dd>Machaut et l'ancienne forge<br>
Marc Mauillon / Vivabiancaluna Biffi / Pierre Hamon<br>
<i><a href="elq0607.htm">Eloquentia 0607</a></i></dd>
</dl>

